{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/820","id":4105113158,"node_id":"PR_kwDOSbOoU870rw5G","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/820","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/820.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/820.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/820","number":820,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Route local path discovery through find","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\n- route explicit local filesystem discovery requests through a seed-defined `find` command before shared capability and web-search routing\n- distinguish Desktop, home/computer, and current-directory scopes, plus file/folder predicates, across English, Russian, Hindi, and Chinese\n- generate safe fuzzy filename patterns for natural names such as `hive-mind-control center`, while preserving open-web `find` requests as web searches\n- cover the OpenAI Chat/Responses and Anthropic protocol surfaces used by Agent, OpenCode, Codex, and Claude\n- add a real four-client E2E harness and an OpenCode TUI transcript verifier based on `link-foundation/command-stream`\n- preserve the investigation, self-authored requirement, raw dialogs, TUI frames, test logs, and changelog fragment\n\nFixes #819.\n\n## Reproduction and result\n\nBefore this change, the reported prompt:\n\n```text\nFind hive-mind-control center folder on my desktop\n```\n\nfell through to `websearch`. The new regression test first pinned that failure and now verifies a single local command equivalent to:\n\n```sh\nfind \"${FORMAL_AI_DESKTOP_DIR:-$HOME/Desktop}\" -type d \\( -iname '*hive*mind*control*center*' ... \\) -print -quit\n```\n\nAgainst an isolated Desktop fixture, that command returns `Desktop/Archive/hive-control-center`. No web tool is called. Open-web requests such as “Find information online…” remain routed to `websearch`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `cargo test --verbose` — all integration groups and doctests pass; main unit corpus: 1,959 passed, 0 failed, 2 ignored\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings`\n- `cargo fmt --check`\n- file-size, hardcoded-language, i18n, language-parity, language-coverage, intent-coverage, web-TDZ, and web hardcoded-UI audits\n- issue #819 unit tests exhaust every seeded action/scope/kind phrase and execute the generated command against a real isolated fixture\n- protocol integration tests cover Agent/OpenCode Chat Completions, Claude Anthropic Messages, and Codex Responses schemas\n- release-binary E2E passes for real Agent, OpenCode, Claude, and Codex CLIs with the complete `user -> find -> tool result -> final answer` sequence\n- real OpenCode TUI capture passes frame deduplication and full dialog-structure verification through `command-stream`\n\n## Evidence\n\n- [Issue #819 case study](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/tree/issue-819-ebe5e6322d6c/docs/case-studies/issue-819)\n- [Four-client and TUI run](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/blob/issue-819-ebe5e6322d6c/docs/case-studies/issue-819/raw-data/e2e/four-client-and-tui.log)\n- [Deduplicated OpenCode TUI transcript](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/blob/issue-819-ebe5e6322d6c/docs/case-studies/issue-819/raw-data/e2e/opencode-tui/tui-transcript.json)\n- [Requirements trace](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/blob/issue-819-ebe5e6322d6c/docs/case-studies/issue-819/requirements.md)\n\nThis is behavioral routing and test-infrastructure work rather than a visual UI change, so there is no before/after screenshot; the committed TUI frames are the relevant UI evidence.\n","created_at":"2026-07-22T04:15:33Z","updated_at":"2026-07-22T06:13:07Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"0500de93fe4c2a74fdd79c3363a5c3307447eb26","assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":true,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/820/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/formal-ai/pulls/820/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assist